 vaguely. “And you—so you aren’t here for long?”

“I’ll probably leave tomorrow. I dropped in to see you for just a few minutes. Tonight I still have to—”

“Sit down, please, sit down.…”

Serafim sat down. They remained silent for a while. They were both thirsty.

“We were talking about books,” said Serafim. “What with one thing and another I just don’t have the time for them. On the train, though, I happened to pick something up, and read it for want of anything be